	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There's no feature like that, really.  Maybe if the PPU's output and NMIs are disabled, and the program just sat on a "here: JMP here" in (internal) RAM.  Then it could be 'woke up' by an external IRQ.
<br />
<br />I doubt it would save much power though, if any at all.  It would put a stop to cartridge memory reads at least.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


