		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, it's possible to install a device on NES to cutoff the video/audio output signals via 4017h port. A proper blueprint wouldn't be so hard. I don't know the GBA sleep mode though, but I believe it's possible.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
